inn1.comm: fullish and slid across the right-hander, Guptill pushes forward and his drive is strong enough to burst through the hands of short cover
124kph, a touch slower on middle and leg, Guptill reads it and nudges towards midwicket

could have been a strike in the first over! Instead the tentative inside edge dribbles away to fine leg. Brownlie seemed he was very wary of the ball cutting back in, but instead it kept on with the angle. Good lines from Tanvir
worked off the pads this time to deep square leg
gets forward to a good length ball on middle and nudges it to short midwicket
back of a length and a shade outside off, Guptill has sized up the line and leaves
tapped to mid-on as Brownlie inches forward to a fuller ball on middle
fuller and a bit outside off, slid away to deep third man. More of a thick outside edge
he's hit his lines quite well, but Guptill must be given credit here. Shuffled across on off stump and once he realised the ball was outside his eyeline, he pulls his bat away
back of a length and on and around fifth stump, Guptill shoulders arms again
tucks him up on middle and leg, Guptill closes the face and works the ball to short midwicket
tapped away just in front of square leg as Irfan strays a bit on the pads
a solid stroke into the covers as Brownlie hopes to take advantage of a fuller ball with some width. But he finds cover
shortish and outside off, sliced off the open face towards the covers
brings him forward on fourth stump and Brownlie checks his drive towards mid-off
authoritative thump from Brownlie as he is given width outside off. Frees his hands and uses some impressive bottom-hand strength to send the ball scurrying through the covers
back of a length and outside off, pushed to mid-off
serenely driven to the left of mid-off as Brownlie moves confidently forward to a good length ball and uses the full face of the bat
shortish on middle and leg, Guptill works it towards square leg
139kph, struck him on the thigh. Irfan beats the batsman for pace, and the bounce is quite disconcerting for Guptill as well. He was looking to flick towards square leg, but is foiled
pushed through the covers off the back foot with Guptill moving deep in his crease and using an open face to find the gap
beaten outside off! Brownlie has no feet against this lifter outside off and throws his bat at it. The intended punch into the covers though does not pan out
this is full on middle and leg, whipped to mid-on
employs a straight bat against a good length ball on off stump and finds mid-off
stretches forward to a good length ball that is around fifth stump and defends
back of a length delivery strays down the leg side. Guptill cannot reach with his flick
slashed through the covers. Both the openers are thriving on width and the easy-paced nature of the pitch. Gets forward and thumped the ball. No danger of swing around here
back of a length on fourth stump, defended. Line seems to be the most important aspect to bowling in Abu Dhabi today
gets forward to a short of a good length ball and defends right under his eyes
waits on the shortish ball on leg stump and tucks it past the right of short midwicket
advances on the bowler, who tucks him up on the pads to lessen his ability to free the arms. Glanced for a single to long leg
opts for the short ball on middle and leg, Brownie ducks under it
fuller ball on middle, tapped back at the bowler and Irfan manages to get down in time
stays beside the back of a length delivery and punches to mid-off

goes for the pull, and manages to get three. He did not look in control of it at all, not enough room for the stroke, the ball was also on its way up and he had to drag if from outside off. Luckily for him, there is no one at deep midwicket
full face of the bat is presented to a good length ball and Guptill's timing is good enough to send the ball to the long-off boundary
back of a length on off stump, defended
clipped off his ankles its fine enough to beat deep square leg. Line goes wrong, batsman gets an easy put away. New Zealand are managing to get through the pressure
through the man at cover! Tanvir goes around the wicket, but it is still stand and deliver stuff from Brownlie. Sizes up a shortish delivery outside off and drills it through. Well timed
very acute angle on middle and leg, Brownlie uses it to clip the ball to deep midwicket
closes the face on a fuller ball on middle and manages to get it through to deep midwicket. Bottom-hand dominance again
stands up tall behind a shortish delivery outside off and pushes to short cover
through extra cover. Powered it through as the back of a length ball comes at a lovely pace for him to push his weight back, wait for it and then pounce
good length ball outside off, tapped to mid-off
short and wide, Brownlie has been strong through that region and out comes the chop through the covers. There's been this boundary ball far too often
back of a length on off stump, tucked to mid-on
full on off stump, Brownlie times a lovely drive down the ground but Anwar gets his left hand down in time

a touch slower outside off, that's a pretty decent ploy with Brownlie thriving on the bowler's pace, goes to punch through the covers and gets a bit of an inside edge. Barely any footwork, but his ploy of staying beside the ball has worked so far
back of a length and outside off, sliced into the covers
leans forward to a fuller ball outside off and directs it to mid-on
good length ball slid outside off, Guptill is content to let it through
shortish and outside off, Guptill gets a bottom edge as he tries to tap the ball to mid-off
instinctive decision to pull a shortish ball that did not quite give him enough room. So the ball only goes as far as short midwicket
123kph, slower, good length ball on middle and leg. Defended
short and on the hips, Guptil goes for a tuck and picks out the lone man at short fine leg. Wears an embarrassed smile as he realises he's politely left a boundary pass him by
134kph, shortish on off stump, Brownlie keeps to the crease to try and drill the ball into the off side. Gets an inside edge back at the bowler, who feigns a throw
amazing work with the wrists. A touch overpitched on middle stump and it could have been driven straight down the ground, but Brownlie opts to show off his strength through midwicket. Lovely balance

this time he does go down the ground, although off a mistimed drive. Irfan lumbers to his left, dives and throws off balance. Meanwhile, the two batsman have collided near the middle of the pitch and a run-out opportunity might have just gone a-begging. Guptill was several yards away from the keeper's end but the throw was inaccurate and barely had any pace
back of a length on off stump, defended
full on leg stump, nudged to deep square leg
fullish on off stump, pushed to mid-on
flighted on leg stump, Guptil stretches to tap the ball to long-on. Conscious to keep a straight bat there
flighted on off stump, with a hint of turn away. Defended
tosses the ball a little further up than normal, Brownlie reaches the pitch and drives through extra cover
closes the face too early as the angle of the fuller delivery and the late turn has Guptill offering a leading edge to the bowler
closes the face again and this time manages to push the ball towards midwicket
leans forward and drives with an open face between cover and point
129kph, too straight and the batsman is able to clip the ball to deep midwicket
uses his height to get on top of a shortish delivery a shade outside off and push it back at the bowler
good length ball brings Guptill forward with a drill to mid-off
133kph, back of a length and a shade outside off, tapped back at the bowler. Tight line from Anwar
good length ball outside off, pushed to mid-off
powerfully driven to cover as Guptill stretches forward to an almost shortish ball outside off
flighted on leg stump, he isn't able to work it away behind square
gets down the track, makes room for himself and drives inside out into the covers
good length ball on off stump, defended
slid down the leg side, Guptill cannot connect with his flick
this time he manages to tuck the ball through to deep square leg
tossed up on off stump, he drives to long-off
skids on to leg stump, the batsman was a touch caught in the crease as he went for a flick and gets a feather. Just enough to have the ball wandering away to the long leg boundary
top-class stroke from Guptil. Rocked back to a short ball with a bit of width and hit it so hard it burst through the man at cover. There is protection in the deep though
good length ball outside off, defended stoutly
pushed to long-on as he uses a closed face against a good length ball
stays beside a shortish ball outside off and drives to cover
lands a slower yorker a shade outside off, the batsman manages to adjust from his original intention to drive through the covers and settle for digging the ball out
full on off stump, drilled to the covers
tossed up on off stump, driven with the full face to long-off
slid into the pads, nudged to midwicket
rocks back to punch a shortish ball around the off stump to long-off
looped up on off stump, defended
worked away off his legs to the left of deep square leg. This is good work from the openers, getting the strike rotating against spin
shortish and outside off, slapped into the covers
good length ball on off stump, Guptil was looking to close the face but then adjusts in time
shortish and a shade outside off, but Guptill takes it on the up and slapped it through extra cover. Dangerous stroke with a man lurking at short cover, but he does strike the ball hard
fuller on middle and leg, driven to long-on
good work by Akmal at cover as he rushes to his right and dives. Brownlie rocks back and ensures he has enough room to bring his hands down through the line of the ball
full on off stump, pushed back at the bowler
offcutter bowled full and outside off, Guptill drives to long-on
uses the open face and slices the ball from off stump towards point
magnificent shot from Brownlie as he gets down the track and is conscious of getting outside the line of the ball to give him enough room to lift over extra cover.
pushed through on middle and leg, defended

caught at short midwicket! a soft dismissal for Brownlie as he went back back to a shortish ball and whipped it. Only he forgot to keep it down and Akmal dive forward and to his right to cling on to a good catch. Barely any celebration from Afridi. And drinks are on the field
tossed up on middle, Williamson defends cautiously
pushed down the leg side and Guptill cannot quite reach with his flick
fuller delivery outside off, Guptill stretches forward and drives to deep cover
lets the good length ball come on and runs it off the open face to deep third man
smeared away through point. Guptill adds a little bit of finesse to his power when he opens the face at the right time to send a shortish ball, only a bit outside off, to the boundary
back of a length on fourth stump, worked to long-on
has some width to free his arms and Williamson takes advantage with a drive through the covers
slapped to cover, but the area is well populated. Guptill has been severe there today
drags his length short and Williamson spots it early and cracked it through midwicket. Solid pull shot from the New Zealand captain. Afridi kicks the turf at his mistake
tossed up outside off and Williamson gets to the pitch and pushes towards cover
sliced towards point
flighted on middle and leg, Williamson defends with bat and pad tight together
nudged towards midwicket, who is on the 30-yard circle and affords the single
driven to the left of mid-off for a single. Afridi did manage to drag the batsman to play outside off, but Guptill countered it by ensuring bat and pad were close
lobs up a friendly full toss on leg stump, Williamson punches to long-on
short and wide this time and the batsman looks a touch awkward while reaching the ball, but Williamson has still timed it well enough to beat point and hit the boundary
pierces the gap at point again as Williamson jumps back, makes some room and gain two off another short ball outside off
lunges forward and drives the low full toss to long-off
how has that missed?! Guptill has played all around a full toss and is very lucky to secure an inside edge that directs onto his right boot and dribble away to the long leg boundary
sliced through the covers to retain strike
pushed through on middle and leg, Guptill is swift enough to defend
stays back to a flatter delivery on off stump, punched to extra cover. Shehzad is the man there and he pulls off a diving save to his right
looped up on leg stump, Guptill had sized it up for a launch but decides against it and defends. Good job too. There was some dip there
very quick and very flat on leg stump, Guptil blocks
another inside edge from Guptill as he is slow to defend a good length ball outside off. Failed to pick the googly
flighted on leg stump, Guptill turns the ball behind square leg

back of a length and outside off, slid to deep third man to raise an important fifty for himself and the team. He did mention that the top-order needed to set a foundation before this game and is doing just that
back of a length and outside off, left through to the keeper
shortish on middle and leg, tapped to the left of midwicket
full and a shade outside off, Williamson is beaten by the ball holding up in the pitch and his drive lobs up, but also lands short of mid-off
lifts from back of a length, but it has slid down leg. Williamson has jumped across to off stump and shoulders arms
full and outside off, pushed to mid-off
pokes and misses outside off. Williamson was nowhere near in a position to play that ball, whose angle beats him
this is shortish and outside off, slapped into the covers
tossed up outside off, Guptill reaches to the pitch and defends
the line strays down leg and Guptill loads up for a sweep. Too full to go through with the shot
nailed it this time. Another poor ball from the part-timer as he offers the perfect length and line outside leg stump for Guptill to sweep
makes him reach outside off with a loopy delivery outside off and possibly because of that, Guptill mistimes to point
stays back to a good length ball outside off and blocks
no slip and Guptill is able to open his face and slide the ball towards third man. Was catchable
back of a length on off stump, Guptill is a bit cramped as he pushes to mid-off
good length ball outside off, forced to the left of cover. But he can't quite time it
shortish and outside off, drilled through to the sweeper on the off side
lovely stroke from Williamson as he goes back and taps the shortish ball outside off through the covers. Pulled right out of the manual
punched to the sweeper as he lets a back of a length ball outside off come on to him
back of a length and directed down leg, Guptill can't play the flick but will enjoy a wide

succumbs to the left-armer's angle! Not enough room for the slice behind point and Guptill has to walk back, dare I say, a tad disappointed. Good bowling from Tanvir though as he hit a good length and pushed the ball across. The batsman tried to do too much with it and pays for his greed
slower through the air and tossed up on middle, Williamson blocks
rushes to his left and dives to keep the push from going to long-off
flighted on middle, Williamson is forward after having made some room and blocks
a touch short and wide, but Williamson's chop finds cover
on the pads and Williamson works it away calmly to long-on
tossed up on middle, Taylor nudgles to long-on and secures the single that was almost gifted to him
takes a very open stance and walked right across on off stump to get hit on the thigh. Appeal from Tanvir, but it had pitched down leg. Leg bye to square leg
good length ball angled across, Taylor presses forward to block
full on middle, Taylor has planted his leg across on off stump and times a flick through wide mid-on. Irfan catches up with it
good length ball on off stump, kept out safely
good length ball steered across the right-hander, Taylor leaves
fullish on off stump, pushed to mid-off
gets down the track, Sohail tries to tuck him up with a flatter ball down leg but Williamson's fast hands adjust. Nudged to midwicket
keeps to the crease and pushes the ball down to long-on
a shade short and Taylor is set up for the cut. Finds point though
tossed up on off stump, defended
fuller delivery on fourth stump, but Taylor spots a cut here as well. Gets an inside edge and soft hands ensures it doesn't threaten the stumps
good length ball eased into the covers
back of a length and outside off, Williamson carves the ball towards point and Akmal misfields. Captain doesn't like that
width outside off and Taylor looks perfectly at home slicing the ball through to the sweeper outside off
that's slower, on a length and a shade outside off. Williamson opens the face to run it to the left of point. And again Akmal looks awkward behind it
full on of stump, Taylor nudges to the right of mid-on and sets off. Tanvir was the man and despite the direct hit, Taylor was well home at the bowler's end
slower, fuller ball outside off. Williamson lets it come on and slides if off the open face to deep third man
good length ball, defended into the covers
gets down the track, but is cramped for room as Sohail pushes the ball on leg stump.
nicely flighted on off stump and Williamson drives to long-off.
short, and turning further away. Taylor is camped on the back foot and taps it towards the covers
flowing drive to long-off as Williamson leans forward and ensured he gets leg side of the ball
worked to long-on as he steps forward to the pitch of a flighted ball on middle
gets down the track, but Sohail does not let Williamson get under it. Pushed through wider outside off to limit his ability to time the ball because he had to reach out

misjudged at deep midwicket! It was possibly the worst ball that could have got a wicket. Lobs up a terrible full toss that Taylor slogs. Tanvir was the man down there and he hurtled in only to realise the ball was going to lob him. Leaps up desperately, but to no avail. Goes down as a drop, that
leans forward to block a tossed up ball on off stump
flighted outside off, driven through extra cover
gets to the pitch and defends on off stump
gets down the track and turns a flighted delivery into a full toss. Driven to long-off
turn to claim the outside edge! Lovely piece of bowling to end the over as Shehzad loops the ball up and in on off stump and then gets it to rip just enough
gets down the track, has to adjust to a flatter ball outside off and slices to point
pushed through on middle and leg, Williamson drives towards long-on. But since Taylor had got in the way of the bowler, who was trying to field the ball, he says no to the single
gets down the track and drives to long-off
fuller delivery outside off, Taylor defends with an open face and gets a bit of an outside edge
slid onto the pads and he hits it as Taylor misses a flick. But the ball would have slid down leg
flighted outside off, defended
nimble footwork gets him down to the pitch of the ball and that means he can hit against the turn towards long-on

no slip and Taylor gets lucky with an outside edge! Beautiful bowling from Shehzad as he gets the ball to drift in and then dip and then turn. A perfect legspinner, especially with the batsman reaching for it with a drive
drags it short and Taylor cuts to point
flighted on middle, Taylor taps it down to long-on
length ball on middle, Williamson goes back and punches to long-off
oh, that's well done. It was tossed up on leg stump and Taylor worked the ball deftly through midwicket who was too far back and picks up two
flatter ball on middle, Williamson pushes towards midwicket
gets down the track and almost too close to the pitch of a flatter ball on off stump and drives to long-off
pushed through on off stump, and was it the googly? No, just the slider. Taylor was uncertain behind it and enjoys an inside edge
gets down the track and whips the ball to deep midwicket
flighted on leg stump, defended
pushed through on off stump, Taylor protects his stumps
gets down the track and Williamson has launched it through the covers. Confident footwork against spin, and he was always looking to hit with the turn as was evident by his moving outside leg
runs down and flicks it to long-on
good length ball on the pads, clipped towards long-on
too much loop on this and Taylor turns a full toss to deep square leg
pushed through the covers as he gets forward to drive the flighted, and turning delivery, outside off
flatter and quicker delivery on leg stump, punched to long-on
gets down the track and slaps a flatter ball outside off to deep point
tossed up outside off, driven to long-off
keeps to his crease and pushes a flatter delivery on off stump down to long-off
flighted delivery on off stump has been tucked to long-on
slower through the air and the ball turns just enough as well. Williamson gets a bit of an outside edge on the drive and picks up a single through the covers
short and wide, Taylor's rasping cut though is stopped by a leaping Shehzad at point. That will be drinks
shortish and cramping him on middle and leg, pushed to mid-on
117kph, goes short, and a shade slower as well, Williamson pulls and keeps it down to the left of short fine leg. Irfan is the man there and he dives almost face first at the ball
stands up tall behind a back of a length ball and punches to mid-off. Races across for the single as well
back of a length on off stump, pushed to mid-off
another slower ball, but it's length goes wrong. Too short and Williamson has waited for it and pulls it strongly to the deep midwicket boundary
fuller ball, clipped away off his pads to deep midwicket again
full on off stump, pushed past mid-off and that's enough to find the boundary. Beautiful placement from the New Zealand captain to bring up his fifty
no slip and the outside edge sails away to deep third man. There's been a few of these going around today
nicks off! No feet from Taylor as he threw his hands at a fuller delivery outside off and the outside edge is fine enough for the wicketkeeper to control it
fuller ball on off stump, defended carefully
goes short and angles it at the body, Anderson works it off his thighs, and I mean right off his thighs, to square leg

beaten outside off and there's that weapon Irfan can summon at will - extra bounce. It leapt off a good length and the angle across the right-hander was enough to lure a tentative poke from Williamson
good length ball on leg stump, Anderson pushes to mid-on
width on offer and it's been sliced away to the sweeper. Shouldn't give away easy runs like that to a new batsman

through mid-off, was it the captain? It was a fuller ball outside off and Williamson loads up for a push. Hit a bit uppishly and it really should have been stopped by Afridi. Slides on his knees, but fails to reach out far enough
good length ball on off stump, defended
back of a length and outside off, punched to the covers
shot! Another straight drive from the New Zealand captain and it's from the top draw as well. Good length on off stump has been firmly struck to the boundary

what a ball! Irfan's extra bounce has Anderson in all sorts of trouble! Jags back in off a short length and the batsman was looking to tuck it away before realising it was getting too big on him and was trying to drop his wrists. Big appeal from the bowler and keeper as Sarfraz pouches the ball, but the deflection was off the shoulder
full on leg stump, turned to mid-on
shuffles outside off and drills a low full toss to mid-off
beaten outside off as Irfan gets the good length ball to grip into the pitch and cut away off the seam. Rolled his fingers there
full on leg stump, clipped to midwicket
pushed through on middle, Afridi clips through midwicket
goes around the wicket, but Anderson has played a remarkable dab to the third man boundary. Let the ball come on and plants the open face as it turns into him
looped up outside off and Anderson is tempted into a slog sweep. Misses it completely
stays back to a good length ball and punched to long-on
saw Williamson coming down and bowled quicker and flatter on middle, worked to deep midwicket
gets down the track to a flighted ball on off stump and blocks
flighted outside off, Anderson slices it through the covers
tossed up on leg stump, driven to the right of long-on. Hafeez races in and keeps it to a single
length ball wanders away too far down leg
fired in outside off, Anderson backs away and slaps it through the covers. Hafeez does well again as he races to his right and dives. Great work
slog sweep and Anderson has heaved it over probably the longest boundary at the ground. Hit with the turn, and though Sohail was bowling around the wicket to limit that very stroke, he cannot succed
flatter on middle and off, clipped away to deep square leg
flatter and fuller on off stump, Anderson drives to long-off
goes back and clips the ball towards midwicket
backs away to a shortish ball, but with it turning in at him his cut shot ends up bunted down the ground
tossed up on middle, driven to long-on
gets down the track and nudges a length ball off his pads to square leg
flighted on off stump, slid away through point
tapped into the covers and picks up the single
taken at long-on! It was overpitched enough for him to go through with the loft down the ground, but it almost seemed like he'd checked the stroke. Only managed to pick out Akmal
good length ball outside off, sliced in front of point to get off the mark
back of a length and on off stump, Williamson tucks it to deep square leg
114kph, a touch slower and wider outside off, Latham drives to deep cover
goes short and Williamson has pulled it to the square leg boundary, with a bit of help from Nasir Jamshed. He had raced to his right, and ended up running past the ball
seeks the yorker, but it ends up a low full toss on middle which Williamson pushes to long-on
flatter and quicker on off stump, clipped wide of long-on
wanted to sweep, but the line was a bit too far outside off and it was rather quick as well. Adjusts with a push to cover
gets down and taps the flatter delivery to cover again
gets down to the pitch and drives a flighted ball outside off to long-off
flighted on the pads, Latham clips it to the right of short fine leg
advances on the bowler and drives the length ball to long-on. That's the end of Afridi's spell. Decent one too
rushes at a length ball on middle and seems to drive outside the line of it. Sneaks through bat and pad and onto the keeper
slower short ball, but Williamson had committed to the pull too early and cannot adjust. Struck on the right bicep, I think after he had gone through with the shot
moves outside off this time and Wiliamson has squirted a very full delivery to deep square leg. Had to drag it, and gets a very thick inside edge

low full toss, with a touch of curl in. Williamson pushes to long-on and seeks a couple. Not there with Akmal rushing in so quickly. Anwar cannot collect the throw cleanly, and Williamson wanted to steal the strike again. But I think it was the keeper who was quick to back up
good length ball outside off, tapped towards the covers and runs. Younis aims at the stump, but misses. Had only one stump to aim at, and it was only a millimeter short!

runs down the track, Anwar bowls short and wide. Williamson slaps it over point and two men race after it. Shehzad gets to the ball first and Haris cannot stop his momentum. Trips over Shehzad's leg, but there doens't seem to be too much damage done. Except for his pride. Afridi yells, "Come on, yaar!"
thick outside edge races away towards the third man boundary until Hafeez intervenes. Williamson had charged down the pitch to slap the ball over the covers
short and wide outside off, slapped away to deep point.
fuller delivery on off stump, defended into the covers and picks up another rapid single. Akmal misses this time
short and wide, Williamson has flat-batted it to the extra cover boundary. He'd been making room for himself for a while now and benefits from it
gets down and outside leg again, but Irfan follows Williamson. Short ball rears up at his shoulder, before Williamson pulls in self-preservation to mid-on
sliced to deep third man for a couple of runs and Williamson will have the strike in the next over
short and wide outside off to try and put Williamson off, but he is still able to crack the ball to deep cover. Might have been the slower short ball
lets the ball through his fingers! Shehzad is the man at point, took his eyes off the ball and gifts Williamson a second run. Williamson is on his haunches as he catches his breath for a bit
slower short ball outside off, Williamson bunts it to mid-off. Back on his haunches and breathing hard
makes some room and slices the shorter ball outside off to the man at deep cover
too wide outside off and he's been called for it
shortish on off stump, Latham half-pulls, half-whips to long-on
yorker on off stump, Williamson has backed away and digs the ball out to long-on

converts the seventh fiftty in nine innings into a hundred with a powerful pull to deep square leg! Jumps outside off and takes advantage of the natural bounce Irfan gets. What a calculated stroke, but boy does he look tired!
full and a shade outside off because Williamson had jumped way to the right of his stumps. Manages a leg bye
sliced away to deep point
creamed through extra cover! The bowler might have expected Williamson to leap outside off again, but he stayed perfectly still and laced the fuller ball outside off to the boundary
and when he goes for the slog over midwicket, he misses out. How many times have we seen that happen to orthodox batsmen?
banged in short and outside off, Williamson moves across to it and pulls to deep midwicket
gets down the track and toe-ends a slap to mid-off

slapped over mid-off, but Akmal has pulled off a lovely chase. Slid beside the ball and flicked it back before it touched the boundary. Too short from Tanvir and Williamson had made room to free his arms despite the bowler bowling around
drilled past mid-off! Another correct stroke fetches him a boundary. Beautiful timing and even better placement from Williamson as he moved inside the line to drive through the line
belted down to long-on, but Williamson at the non-strikers' end was in danger of being struck. Perhaps it did graze his right arm
full and angled in on middle, heaved to deep midwicket, and Williamson has slipped while taking a single and that is all he has to settle for
backs away to slice the ball over point, but he misses. He's running on fumes, Willliamson.
slower ball sent down too wide outside off
moved outside off and Williamson has picked up the full toss and deposited it to long leg

showed off all his stumps while trying to pull a shortish delivery to long leg. That was very close to toppling the stops, but it lobbed over them and beat the keeper. Just enough glove to find the boundary too
full toss on middle, swatted to long-on
hit on the grille, coming off the bat as he sought to lap sweep! Runs to the other end and gives a thumbs up. It was a full toss outside off
bowled off the last ball of the innings. Good yorker from Irfan, and Williamson helped it out by exposing his stumps. in an effort to clip the ball to fine leg

inn2.comm: beaten first ball, a bit of rust showing in Jamshed's game as he fails to move his front foot towards the fuller ball outside off.
that time the footwork didn't matter, with his balance helping him out. As did Henry's length, which was short and allowing him to guide the ball in front of point. A Guptill slide keeps it to three
uses soft hands to drop the short delivery outside off by his feet

what a delivery! Off stump cartwheels as Henry opens Shehzad up! Speared the ball in at a very full length and it curls away late. Shehzad can't quite be blamed for being stuck on the crease against a ball like that. Pushes with his hands and next second, he hears timber!
full and shaping away again. Younis' feet are splayed at the crease as he blocks the ball towards the off side and sets off
nudged away to short midwicket as Jamshed lets the fuller ball come onto him
full on middle and leg, pushed to mid-on. Warms up with a 135 kph delivery
back of a length and outside off, left well alone
148kph, Younis manages to open the face on a full delivery on off stump to find short cover
146kph, low full toss on middle, Younis manages to bunt it to mid-on
143kph, keeps it right up there on off stump, Younis pushes it past the bowler with a very straight bat
low full toss on off stump, pushed back at the bowler and Milne has broken the 150kph barrier in his very first over!
139kph, good length ball, slid into the covers. Jamshed was keen on the single, but Younis wasn't. All's well though as the throw goes awry
very full, but it's on leg stump which Jamshed has picked it away to deep square leg. Smart cricket
shortish on middle and off, pulled to short midwicket
back of a length and slid across the left-hander and he is lured into poking outside off. Nods his head and practices a leave after the fact
141 kph, aimed at the base of off stump but Jamshed digs it out
fullish on middle, perhaps with a hint of tail back in. Jamshed works it in front of square leg
back of a good length on off stump, defended to short midwicket
147kph, taps a good length ball from the crease to mid-on. Sucker ball outside off might be worth a try with his feet not moving much
that's too short and too straight, Jamshed takes advantage of it despite it's pace being at 151 kph, almost reaches the square leg boundary
151kph, fullish and outisde off, Younis wants to drive to mid-off but gets it off the inside part of the bat
back of a length with a touch of cut back in, Younis steps across to protect his stumps and leaves the 149 kph delivery
152.3 kph, solidly behind a good length ball on off stump.
139kph, opens the face to a shortish delivery and runs it to cover
140kph, shortish and a shade outside of, defended
141kph, digs it in short and it soars over the left shoulder of the uninterested Jamshed
beautifully struck! Watched the 141 kph delivery right onto the blade as he stepped forward and drives the ball through extra cover. Stands and admires
beaten this time as Henry shortens his length and watches the batsman poke outside the off stump. Very uncertain that time as the ball seams away with the angle
strays on the pads and Jamshed had cracked it to the square leg boundary. He's got some amazing hands, although admittedly that was a very poor ball
152kph, back of a length and a shade outside off, Younis gets an inside edge, onto boot and into the off side for a single
149kph, outside edge with Jamshed a touch late on the back foot block. Just enough seam away from the bat, and  the pace he generates means the ball singes away to deep third man
bouncer at 151kph! Younis was leaping off his feet and swaying away from the line. Top quality batting against top quality pace and then nonchalantly chews his gum
152 kph, the two-card trick gets the edge, but Taylor's spilled it! Younis was caught in the crease as he pokes outside off. Healthy nick that was going low to first slip's left. Can't convert it
back of a length and outside off, left well alone this time
149kph, fuller delivery outside off, driven to cover
back of a length on off stump, carefully defended
full on off stump, pushed to mid-on
pokes outside off, beaten and Ronchi's having troubles behind the stumps this time! The ball swung late to beat both batsman and swings even further as it comes to the keeper
back of a length on off stump, defended
full on off stump, Jamshed drives calmly to mid-off. He's managed to time the balls quite well in this little innings
fuller delivery on middle, Jamshed tucks it to short midwicket who parries the ball towards mid-on
150kph, picked away off his pads, but he finds square leg
150kph, goes wide of the crease to deliver a full ball on off stump, clipped to short midwicket
149.9kph goes for the bouncer, but it was dug into the middle of the deck and Jamshed had enough time to get under it. Square leg umpire says that has too much height though
shortish on off stump, thuds into Jamshed's bat at 151 kph as he defends
back of a length on off stump, was trying to clip it to the leg side but skews it away to mid-off. Too quick

shortish on off stump, Jamshed taps it down the pitch and was searching for a single but Milne leaps to his right away from his followthrough and sends him diving back into his crease with a throw at the stumps
144kph, shortish and at the body, Jamshed gets an inside edge onto his body and down to long leg

cut back in at 137 kph delivery and Jamshed was rooted to the crease while looking to push into the covers. Huge gap between bat and pad, and it was almost taken advantage of. Ends up an inside edge towards square leg
pushed into the covers off the back foot
opens the face and slides the shortish ball down to deep third man
that was uppishly struck towards cover, but it falls short of the man diving forward. This was full with a bit of width and Younis thought he could evade the stranglehold.
137kph, fuller and a shade outside off, tapped into the coveres
full on middle and leg, Younis clips to midwicket
starts off with almost a yorker a shade outside off, Jamshed skews it to short third man
good length ball outside off, Jamshed pushes through the covers
good length ball on and around off stump, defended with some nervous footwork
shortish on off stump, steered to deep third man to get off strike
there we go, this was what he was waiting for. The wide half-volley that been crashed through the covers. See, if you wait long enough, you will get those
good length ball on off stump, defended
shortish on middle and leg, turned away to long leg
tucks him up on off stump and Younis can only defend down the pitch off the back foot

flays it over a leaping point fielder. Very powerfully struck as he takes advantage of a short and wide delivery from Anderson. Leapt off the square and beat the man inside the circle and split the sweeper and deep third man as well

moves around the wicket for a good length ball angled in at off stump, Younis steps forward to block and is surprised by a little nip back in. Gets an inside edge onto pad and it deflects to the right of the keeper
short and wide, Jamshed cracks it straight at point. Missed ou there and he knows it
good length ball outside off, guided to point
fuller ball outside off, driven to mid-off
goes short and a shade outside off, Younis looks for a pull and then rolls his wrists as ball makes contact rather high on the bat to keep it down to midwicket
short ball slides down leg, would have been a wide, but it's been called no-ball because Mitch Mc has clipped the stumps at the bowler's end with his bowling hand
brilliant short ball and he beats Younis for sheer pace. Was looking to pull, off the front foot as well, can't manage it
too full, too wide and Younis has slammed it through the covers. So well struck that it burst through the fielder inside the circle
goes short and slides it across the right-hander, who leaps up and runs the ball to deep third man
right up there on middle as Jamshed clips to long leg. The pressure has been eased a bit with the bowling changes. Wonder if it's time for Dan the Man...
back of a length and outside off, defended
gets down the track, picks up the length and has deposited it miles beyond long-on. What a way raise the team fifty. Watched it all the way untiil it hit the fence
shortish and a bit too wide for him to reach, especially with his movement away from the ball to try and create room

his footwork has been suspect all through the innings. He was relying solely on his balance and timing so far but this time he's misread an offcutter and has found himself plumb in front. Anderson knew straight away, had a giant grin all through the appeal as the ball gripped in the pitch and veered in at Jamshed to beat the inside edge and hit the back pad in front of all three stumps
back of a length and slid across the right-hander, left alone
good length ball on off stump, defended
fuller delivery on off stump, pushed back at the bowler
clipped off his toes to deep midwicket
shortish on middle, Younis nudges to the right of mid-on
back of a length on off stump, defended towards point
shortish and on the body, Hafeez lets it come on and tickles it to long leg
back of a length on off stump, Hafeez taps it into the covers. Williamson has kept a majority of his men inside the circle so there are no easy singles
shortish and angled into him from around the wicket, clipped away to long leg
fuller delivery and slid across Hafeez from over the wicket, left alone
good length ball on leg stump, defended
fuller ball on fifth stump, pushed towards mid-off
charges at the bowler to try and crash the ball away. Toe ends it and takes a while to recognise where it went.
shortish on off stump, worked to mid-on

takes him out first ball! Hafeez keeps back to a good length ball and plays inside the line. He was looking for a push into the off side with an angled face and ends up nicking to the keeper. Good work form Ronchi. That will be drinks as well
tossed up on off stump, pushed back at the bowler
flighted on off stump, defended
good length ball on off stump, kept out
punched to long-on
goes back to a good length ball to push into the covers
back of a length and outside off, slid to point
drilled to mid-on as Anderson bowls full and on off stump
opens the face, which might be a dangerous tactic with a widish slip in. But he controls it reasonably well and plays with soft hands
fuller ball, sliced towards point
back of a length and outside off, it's the slower ball as well. Sohail tries to dab it to third man and misses
short on off stump, leaps up to tap into the covers
flighted on middle, Younis taps it gently to square leg and picks up an easy single
a bit short and wide, Sohail goes for a cut and gets a toe end that skirts away to the third man boundary. Arm ball ends up favouring the batsmen
good length ball going on with the angle from over the wicket. Sohail closes the face too soon and gets a leading edge
leans forward and tucked to mid-on
flighted on off stump, driven back at the bowler
pushed through on off stump, Sohail taps it through the covers for a single
lobs up a juicy full toss which has been caned to the midwicket boundary. Inviting delivery taken advantage of
flighted on leg stump, pushed down to long-on
quicker delivery on off stump, pushed down to long-on.
goes around the wicket and blocks a well flighted delivery on off stump
pushed to long-on
leans forward to the pitch of this flighted ball on leg stump and drives to long-off
slid down the leg side. Younis can't connect, but will take the extra ball
flighted on middle, driven back at the bowler. Vettori misfields, but there is no single
tossed up on off stump, defended towards the covers. Sohail wanted a run, but is sent back
chips down the pitch and drives to long-off
prefers to stay back to a flighted ball on off stump and clip to midwicket
pushed to a wide mid-on as Vettori goes flatter and quicker on off stump
backs away to try and cut a length ball off leg stump, but finds cover
flighted outside off, Younis drives to long-off
flatter and quicker outside off, Sohail mistimes a cut to long-off
flighted on off stump, Younis flicks back at the bowler
opens the face and slices a flighted delivery into the covers. Again, can't beat the infield
runs down the track and carts a length ball between deep square leg and deep midwicket
there's his favourite stroke, seizes a flighted delivery on the pads and sweeps it to long leg
flighted on middle, driven to long-off
good length ball on off stump, Sohail defends the arm ball

goes down the track and lifts it down long-on's throat! The pressure tells on Sohail as he strikes the ball off the inside edge and gets too much height. Latham had run in a bit too enthusiastically and has to backtrack to get under the ball
flighted on middle, tucked to the right of midwicket
tossed up on off stump, pushed back at the bowler
length ball on middle, Akmal reaches forward to block
starts off with a slower ball, I think. Or maybe it was just his warm up... Defended well on off stump
148kph, fuller ball on off stump, pushed back at the bowler
goes for the bouncer, and it's right over middle as well. Younis ducks under it
147kph, right up there just outside off, Younis blocks it
beaten, for sheer pace! Good length ball outside off, with a little seam away as well. Younis throws his bat at it and does not connect
ducks under another bouncer on middle and collects his second maiden on the match. If his speed has been spectacular, his accuracy has been even more so
flighted on off stump, defended carefully to square leg
gets down the work a length ball to short midwicket
short and wide, Akmal makes it worse with some sharp footwork to make some room and cracks it to the sweeper on the off side
gets down the track and is almost beaten by Vettori pulling the flight back. Pushes at the ball and manages to drive to long-off. Required rate over eight now
seeks a single towards long-off, but Vettori cuts across and dives
goes back and tucks the ball towards short midwicket
full and a shade wide of off stump, Akmal wants to lay into him with a drive. But mistimes to mid-off
149kph, low full toss on middle, clipped to deep midwicket
angled in on off stump, Younis is hurried into a flick by this 148 kph delivery and manages an inside edge to deep midwicket
144kph, short and wide outside off, Akmal guides it to deep third man off the back foot
goes short and a shade outside off, punched to deep cover
goes for a bouncer and forces the batsman to duck under it
gets down the track and pushes the length ball back down the pitch
short ball on off stump, backs away and cuts to deep point
pushed through on off stump, Akmal prefers to stay back and barely manages to keep this out
short of a length, which allows Akmal to back away and cut to deep point
stays back to a good length ball and pushes to mid-on
flighted on off stump, driven to mid-off
fuller delivery outside off, Akmal drives to cover
full on off stump, flayed away through the covers
waits on a fuller ball on off stump and runs it down to point
seeks the base of off stump and ends up with a low full toss, which Akmal pushes to the right of mid-off
goes on the bounce to mid-off as Younis checks his on-the-up drive. Wanted to hit over the top, but realises this good length ball held in the pitch
shortish on off stump, nudged in front of point
goes back to punch a good length ball to long-on
flighted on middle, defended
arm ball on middle, Akmal backs away to punch to long-off
flighted on off stump, driven to long-off
goes back to a short ball and pulls it to deep midwicket. A Henry slide keeps it to two though
flighted on middle, defended

he's been hit on the helmet! Seems to be okay even as Mitch Mc goes up to check. Struck on the grille as he looks to pul lthe short ball on middle. Deflected off the glove as he was so late on the pull
goes for the pull again, and he's timed this no better. Being beaten for pace is Younis, very late on the shot. Lovely direction from Mitch, and good height too
full and wide outside off, drilled to deep cover
good length ball on middle, pushed to mid-off
another short ball on middle and leg, Younis cannot put it away. Mistimes to long leg
short delivery, with just enough width for Akmal to pull in front of midwicket
flighted on leg stump, swept to long leg
flighted on off stump and Younis has slog swept it over the midwicket boundary. Calculated strike from Younis as he realises Vettori is not quite turning the ball today
picked away off middle stump to a clip to long leg. Fifty for Younis. A very painstaking one.
good length ball on off stump, pushed to mid-on
flighted outside off, driven to deep cover
opens the face and slices a tossed up delivery into the covers
full on off stump, Younis gets a thick outside edge to third man
fuller ball on middle and leg, driven to the right of mid-on
goes short and a bit down leg, Younis looks to hook and can't connect. But that was because it soared over the batsman's head
goes short, with a change of action from Mc, hand both of his hands whirling around before he delivered. Pulled ot deep midwicket
cramped up against the short ball on middle and leg, pulled to deep midwicket
full and outside off, sliced to deep third man
good length ball outside off, slid to the right of point
starts around the wicket and bowls a shortish delivery outside off, Younis goes for a chop and gets it off the inside half of the bat and the ball goes back at the bowler
good length ball bunted into the covers for a quick single
length ball outside off, carved towards mid-on. Almost finds Vettori on the full, but it drops just in front of him and he did well to get his body behind it. Very awkward bounce
good length ball on leg stump, slower as well, Akmal clips it to deep square leg
opens the face to try and slice the fuller ball from outside off stump through point. Can't manage it
backs away to a good length ball and taps it through the covers

crack! Younis has unleashed against a loose short ball. It might have been the offcutter. He'd had a change of bat and it seems to be working perfectly. Rocks back and pulls it way over the deep midwicket boundary, off the front foot as well

goes for another slower bouncer, got it around neck-height and outside off to limit Younis' ability to pull the ball. He'd set up for the pull quite early, but has to adjust and manage to find a single to long leg

this time the slower ball is fuller and Akmal has hoisted it way too high! Williamson runs back from mid-off, tracking the ball that always seems to be beating him and he ends up a couple of yards short
run down to third man off the back foot
goes short and slow - legcutter - Younis manages to swipe the ball to deep midwicket and Akmal drags his senior partner for a couple
clipped through midwicket, almost an over full of slower balls
short and wide, despite Anderson bowling around the wicket, Younis cuts to deep point
backs away to a slower, length ball and Younis has sliced it well behind point. Brownlie has a lot of ground to cover to his left, and a full length dive saves a single
full and angled in on off stump, Akmal gets a thick inside edge onto the boot for a single
poor line from Anderson and it skirts off Younis' pads while he tries to tickle the ball to the fine leg boundary. And that's where it ends up
fuller ball on off stump, defended towards mid-off and takes a single
fuller delivery a shade outside off, Akmal looks to run it to third man and misses
goes short, but Younis able to get better power behind the pull for a couple to deep midwicket
yorker on leg stump, tucked to square leg
runs down and belts the short ball to the long-on boundary. He had made room while coming down and then hit through the line. Muscled away
good short ball this time, reaches him quick on middle, Akmal tucks it to short midwicket
low full toss on leg stump, pushed to long-on for a single
this is short, Younis is nowhere in control again as he top-edges a pull. Vettori tries his best to get under it from long-leg but it falls well short of him. Seems to be drinks
short of a good length on leg stump, turned to square leg
slower ball a shade outside off, Akmal drives a touch too early and adjusts mid-way through the shot. Gets a single to mid-off
back of a length and outside off, Younis whips it with great bottom-hand strength to deep midwicket
full on leg stump with the slower ball, Akma chips it to long-on
length ball in the powerplay and Younis has carted it to the square leg boundary. Lovely placement
fuller and outside off, Younis looks to slash it through point and the ball drops just short of a diving Guptill. Younis has ridden his luck today

that is so unfortunate! Younis has caned a straight drive and Mitch Mc manages to get enough of a deflection back onto the stumps, one of which cartwheels on impact, with Akmal backing up! Among the worst dismissals in cricket
slower ball on middle, Younis clips to deep square leg and picks up a couple. Good running from Younis
goes for the bouncer and Younis gloves it down to long leg
goes short and Afridi allows it to sail over his crouched body. Too much height says the ump
runs the short ball from off stump down to third man for a couple
short ball sits up for Afridi to wallop to the square leg boundary. Took it off the front foot as well.Typically powerful strike
another bouncer from Mitch and this time Afridi does not have the room to free his arms. Struck on the glove as he tries to pull
bit of width outside off, chopped towards the covers
lands a yorker just outside off to fool Afridi who was jumping across to put the bowler off. Adjusts to try and drive the ball through the covers, but is beaten
full on off stump, drilled to mid-off. Younis was charging for a single, but was sent back. There was no single there. Williamson looks for the direct hit, but Younis would have been gone had it hit
slower ball on off stump, Afridi knows mid-off is up and he lifts the ball to the straight boundary. Picked up the offcutter and gets just enough bat on it. What you'd call a calculated risk
laps the full toss outside off to long leg. Mitch Mc slips and fumbles there, but it doesn't cost much
backs away, but Anderson ties him up with a yorker on middle
short and outside off, Younis pulls but Anderson at midwicket does great work diving to his right
another slower short ball, Younis spots it and pulls to deep midwicket

huge appeal as the offcutter strikes Afridi in front of the stumps. The umpire says there was bat involved though. Afridi was moving across to open up the leg side and was struck on the top flap of the pad in line with leg stump. Review not taken. Might have been height as well
worked away to square leg for a single
fuller and slower outside off, Afridi tries to cart it to the square leg boundary but plays outside the line. Beaten

pace on this and Afridi has heaved it over the cow corner boundary and Henry has his hands on his head. Overpitched and the captain has launched it just about over the leaping fielder. Brownlie got a hand on it, but he really had no chance
flighted on off stump, tapped into the covers for a single
short and wide, Afridi cracks it to deep cover. Brownlie comes in handy again
sweeps off a length and Afridi has found the boundary at long leg. It was a quick, flat delivery and he's used all that pace to his advantage
pulls the pace off and Afridi taps the ball into the covers for a single. Dare I say, sensible from Afridi?
good length ball on off stump, nudged into the vacant cover field
length and Afridi has backed away and slugged it to the cow corner boundary again. Abu Dhabi has suddenly woken up!
shortish and outside off, tapped to the left of midwicket
short and Afridi has miscued a pull off the front foot to long-on, and then calls for a new pair of gloves
slower ball goes short and outside off, Younis pulls to deep midwicket

goes for a lap sweep, took his eyes off the ball and he ends up wearing it on the grille. Bowler checks on him as he runs through to the non-strikers'. Off the glove and thwack! A bit too short for that shot
slower bouncers galore and Younis is able to pull it to deep midwicket
slants a full ball way wide of off stump. The wide yorker goes wrong because of the Afridi effect
full toss outside off, Afridi has launched it over mid-off and then over the rope. That's the fifty partnership and it's come off 29 balls!
150kph, good length ball on off stump, slid to third man

goes wide the crease and bowls a good short ball, only a shade outside off, Afridi backs away to try and slap it over point or third man. Beaten for pace. 148 kph. He was livid at himself for missing the ball
149kph, good length ball on off stump, tapped into the covers. Has a little word with MIlne at the other end, and the young bowler retorts back. Fiery!
148kph short and wide outside off, the ball swings away after it passes the outside edge
146kph, shortish on middle and leg, tucked to midwicket
142kph, short ball on middle, Afridi mistimes it to long-on with a flat-batted pull. Not too keen to stay in line against Milne
short ball on off stump lifts Younis off his crease to block
short and wide, Younis cracks it to the sweeper and gets on to 99
short and wide, Afridi finds point with his slice. Again, he's timing the ball brilliantly

there it is! He's vindicated himself after a sluggish start. Whip to deep midwicket for a single and gets a hug from his captain and lifts a hand to the dressing room. Very muted celebrations. He knows there's a job to be done. And that strike rate is at 90 now
lovely hands from Afridi. Saw the shortish ball with some width and he dabs past short third man. Off cutter goes wrong for Henry

tips it over! Vettori was the man at short fine leg and leaps up and to his left to try and snaffle the catch. Afridi knew there was only one man at short fine and if he lobbed him there was a boundary. Vettori came so close
Milne has done the trick! The old back-away slash through point ends up as an outside edge to the keeper. What a rollicking innings it has been.
151kph, right up there on off stump, Sarfraz is able to whip it behind deep square leg. There was a bit of tail in there

heaved! What a strike, he's carted a 150 kph length ball almost onto the advertising skirting! Got down on one-knee, loved the extra pace from Milne and used it to his benefit. Gee, this guy has a knack of doing the impossible
goes short and wide, this time Sarfraz is beaten outside off
beautiful! There was a wide slip in place, but Sarfraz has waited for the shortish ball outside off to come onto him and dabbed it away to the third man boundary
145kph, short and outside off, Sarfraz misses with his chop through point
length and outside off, Sarfraz looks to slog it over mid-on, and it was Williamson there, running back and leaping as far as he could to try and grab it. But it has just enough bat to lob him
turned away towards the right of mid-on as Vettori bowls flat and on middle

slower through the air, Sarfraz goes for a sweep and the ball lobs up into the keeper's gloves. Vettori and Ronchi are certain about this. Umpire Raza just stands there, unimpressed. So New Zealand go for a review. The ball certainly deflected off the heel and into Ronchi's hands. I wonder if there is glove though... Very difficult to judge. Can they look at a leg-before, because Sarfraz was in front of all three stumps here. Had a giant stride forward though. Tense, tense, tense decision for third umpire Joel Wilson. Looks like he decides there was no glove. Onto the lbw then, Umpire's call on the leg-before, even with a decent chunk of the ball hitting leg stump...
jumps down the track and whips it to deep midwicket. Another easy two on offer on this large ground
down the track and works the ball towards midwicket and Ronchi gets after it
flat, full and straight. Vettori has toppled Younis and has coolly gone back to the umpire to collect his cap. Wild slog from Younis and he realised his mistake the moment he swung past the ball
that's a back of a length delivery to which Sarfraz opts to slog sweep. Grunts in disgust as he is beaten
short and wide, Sarfraz uses the pace on offer and taps it towards the third man boundary. But Matt Henry down there pulls off a spectacular diving effort. Parried the ball inches from the skirting
good length ball on middle and leg at 150 kph, turned to the right of midwicket
147kph, shortish on off stump, Sarfraz chops it behind him to race across to the other end
too quick for the tailender, who tries to pull a 151 kph short ball and wears it on the thigh pad. Sarfraz races across to steal a leg bye
146kph, short and Sarfraz has struck the pull quite well to deep midwicket. Seven runs off the over.

taken by Ronchi! Just about! Sarfraz is gone and it's a Mitch that turns a match again. Cross-seamed short ball that followed Sarfraz as he moved outside leg to make room for himself. Goes for a pull on instinct and top-edges it straight up. The rest was taken care of by an alert Ronchi
fires it in full on leg stump, clipped to long leg
short on middle, Anwar nudges it to point and finds there is no single
lands a terrific yorker on middle, Anwar does very well to dig it out and take a single
stays around and bowls a yorker on off stump, Tanvir can only tap it through point. Mitch Mc has been a terrific enforcer today
there's the short ball and it skips off the top edge to the third man boundary despite a diving effort from the fielder there. This game is nowhere near over!
beats Tanvir for pace as he goes for a pull, ball leaps off the splice of the bat and falls well short of the long leg fielder rushing in
back of a length and outside off, Anwar backs away to slash and misses. 150 kph, in his final over.
slapped to the long-off boundary! How is that for a counterpunch. Cleared that front leg and got enough bat to beat mid-off and race off
a touch shorter on middle and off, Anwar looks to slap it away again and hits it rather high on the bat. Takes a single as the ball falls short of mid-off

shortish on middle, Tanvir looks to pull and gets an inside edge onto his body. Loud calls of "yeah" as Pakistan take a single. Bowler raced up to try and effect a run-out but was unable to get the ball
148kph, short ball sails over middle stump as he beats Anwar's wild swing. What a spell, 10-2-39-1
around the wicket angle cramps Tanvir, who goes for a huge slog to a fuller ball outside off. Misses
full on middle, Tanvir played a loft over long-on too early and toe-ends it along the ground
a timely boundary for Pakistan as a shortish delivery has leapt off the top edge to the third man boundary.
nails a yorker on leg stump, but Anwar is able to grab a single towards midwicket. Those deep fielders better be alert
heaved to deep midwicket, but there is protection there. Offered length, but wasn't capitalised on
yorker a shade outside off, clipped to deep midwicket
short ball, it's the slower one as well. Tanvir wasn't ready for that and he's missed it. Lovely height on the ball, came up to his neck
low full toss, cracked to the midwicket boundary. Guptill was guarding that region and despite a big dive, it races away
full and on the pads, have to settle for one leg bye as Ronchi runs after it
length ball on middle, heaved to long-on for a couple
beaten! Brilliant effort from Henry! It was back of a length right on top of off stump, the batsman slogs wildly and can't connect
that's it, just a single to long-on and New Zealand have made it 2-2! What a game it has been! And it ends with the bowler nailing a full ball on middle
